<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="415" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.001W64/39</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BRW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-10">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 10, 1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.41 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Emperor of Germany is reported to have crossed into Holland this
                                morning near Maestricht. He was accompanied by a numerous suite and
                                is now staying at Medachten,<note n="1" xml:id="d415fn1">Corrected
                                    to “Amerongen” by a telegram next day.</note> the country place
                                of Count <persName>Bentinek</persName>.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_BRW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>